# C++ formatting rules. C++17 code in this project uses tabs in some legacy
# files but new code follows this style; run `clang-format -i` on changed
# files before sending a PR.
---
BasedOnStyle: LLVM
IndentWidth: 4
ColumnLimit: 100
UseTab: Never
AllowShortFunctionsOnASingleLine: Inline
AllowShortIfStatementsOnASingleLine: Never
AllowShortLoopsOnASingleLine: false
BreakBeforeBraces: Attach
PointerAlignment: Right
SortIncludes: true
IncludeBlocks: Preserve
Language: Cpp
Standard: c++17